From 3e8c36fcf66d6661bd2dd8b715a52ad3dee30b5e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 22 Aug 2025 21:41:19 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Fix TPE PSD for punctured
 channels
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Handle TPE IE formation correctly for punctured 80 MHz channels
with composite AP enabled.

Currently, when bringing up an AP on a punctured 80 MHz channel, the
get_chan_list() API fails with the error "Invalid channel and bw", resulting
in the omission of PSD TPE for subordinate and default client types.
Only EIRP TPE is sent.

This occurs because punct_update_legacy_bw() sets the
bandwidth to CONF_OPER_CHWIDTH_USE_HT (20 MHz or 40 MHz) based
on the punctured channel’s position, and updates seg0 accordingly.
For example, with primary channel 145 and channel 149 punctured, seg0
becomes 145 and only 20 MHz is possible. get_chan_list() then
calculates non11be_start_chan = seg0 - 2 = 143, which is invalid
in 6 GHz, causing the API to fail.

Fix this by setting non11be_start_chan = pri_chan and non_11be_chan_count = 1
when legacy bandwidth becomes 20 MHz (i.e., seg0 == pri_chan), instead
of using seg0 - 2.

This ensures valid channel configuration and enables proper
PSD TPE inclusion in the TPE IE.

Fixes: Ic72a220bd9ca94e ("hostapd: TPE 11AX changes and support for 11BE TPE")
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency:
r21-001-hostapd-TPE-11AX-changes-and-support-for-11BE-TPE.patch

Signed-off-by: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/ieee802_11.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
index 31418a5..4a6fc3a 100644
--- a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
+++ b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
@@ -8337,7 +8337,7 @@ static int get_chan_list(struct hostapd_data *hapd, int *non_11be_start_idx,
 			*non_11be_chan_count = 4;
 			break;
 		case CONF_OPER_CHWIDTH_USE_HT:
-			if (!seg0) {
+			if (!seg0 || (seg0 == pri_chan)) {
 				non11be_start_chan = pri_chan;
 				*non_11be_chan_count = 1;
 			} else {
